column35: Comments
Most birds flying overhead, no NOGA diving or in the water. ~10 HERG trying to get fish out of net during pulling; 1 successfully
Most HERG in the water, no NOGA flying or on water. >10 HERG on top of net trying to get fish out - several successful
Lots of slob and full kelp stuck in net. No bird trying to get fish out of net but HERG following the boat
column36: NOGA, ATPU, CORMO flying, Gulls flying + in the water

column35: Lots of slob and full kelp stuck in net. No bird trying to get fish out of net but HERG following the boat
column36: NOGA, ATPU, CORMO flying, Gulls flying + in the water

column35: No catch but HERG still flying above net and landing on it. Only kelp in net
column36: NOGA flying only. About 30 diving 2.5km SW from were nets are set: 49.453371, -53.983744 at the time of pulling

column35: No catch but HERG still flying above net and landing on it. Only kelp in net
column36: NOGA flying only. About 30 diving 2.5km SW from were nets are set: 49.453371, -53.983744 at the time of pulling

column35: Lots of catch, cloudy skies but not foggy yet no birds around. HERG showed up while we were pulling, stayed on the water throughout pulling but not trying to get fish from net
column36: About 40 NOGA diving 50m from shoreline in front of Bill's house - nowhere near nets

column35: HERG followed us from net 1, GBBG showex up and got fish from net. NOGA flying above only
Very rough waters, could only check net 1. Some birds flying above, none in the water
Very rough waters, could not check net 2. Went by, couple of herrings seem to be in the net, some birds flying above, none in the water
lots of catch, 100s of NOGA flying above net to go to Ladle Cove - all diving, herring-spawning site: 49.479977, -54.037945
lots of catch, 100s of NOGA flying above net to go to Ladle Cove - all diving, herring-spawning site: 49.479977, -54.037945
column36: 2 HERG floating in the water on top of net

column35: Lots of catch, a few herring gulls flying above the net but never touched it. NOGA and CORMO flying nearby
column36: Herring spawning at entrance of harbour yesterday all day and night - turquoise water as evidence + gannets seen diving there all pm on May 20th

column35: Lots of catch, minke circling the net as we approached to pull. A few gulls circling above but lost interest quickly
column36: Herring in both nets visible from the surface

column35: Thousands of NOGA diving right in harbour. 100s around the nets resting on the water
column36: Herring spawning at entrance of harbourat the time of net pulling

column35: Thousands of NOGA diving right in harbour. 100s around the nets resting on the water
column36: Herring spawning at entrance of harbourat the time of net pulling

column35: Thousands of NOGA diving right outside of harbour (~100m from nets). 100s flying over the nets in all direction. HERG taking fish right out of net without difficulty during pull

Thousands of NOGA diving right outside of harbour (~100m from nets). 100s flying over the nets in all direction. Net not pulled, wind picking up and water ++ rough; herring visible in net from surface
Thousands of NOGA diving right outside of harbour (~100m from nets). 100s flying over the nets in all direction.
column36: NOGA had been diving in Hr since early morning

column35: NOGAs dispersed before pulling net, some flew above net. Gulls around the net trying to get fish.
column36: Net full of herring, some fish getting old and soft

column35: NOGAs not diving in or around harbour anymore, herring spawning might be over. Only a few NOGAs flying overhead. Lots of gulls trying to get fish out of net during pulling
5 NOGAs diving 50m away from net. RBGU sitting on net when we arrived, left when other gulls showed up and returned after pulling was over. GBBG from all ages present
No NOGAs diving anywhere near harbour or nets. Gulls following us between nets
Gulls followed from previous net but all nets empty
100s of NOGAs flying in all directions around net. Not diving near net, all diving in front of Bill's house
100s of NOGAs flying in all directions around net. Not diving near net, all diving in front of Bill's house
100s of NOGAs flying in all directions around net, none seen diving
100s of NOGAs flying in all directions around net, none seen diving

3 bycaught NOGAs side by side in net, one caught by bill, other 2 caught by wing - net full of herring, soaked for 36hr (2 nights) because very stormy, high wind and swells the previous day. Only a few gannets seen diving 100m away from net
Net full of herring again but no bycatch. 100s of NOGAs now flying above net, only a dozen 100m away diving
About 30 NOGAs diving 100m away from net. No other NOGA around
